  <brief_title>A Study of Rofecoxib in the Treatment of Post-Operative Pain After Total Knee Joint Replacement (0966-259)</brief_title>
  <official_title>A Study to Compare Pre-Operative Administration of Rofecoxib Vs Post-Operative Administration of Diclofenac or Rofecoxib in the Treatment of Post-Operative Pain After Total Knee Joint Replacement in Patients With Osteoarthritis of the Knee.</official_title>
  <sponsors>
    <lead_sponsor>
      <agency>Merck Sharp &amp; Dohme Corp.</agency>
      <agency_class>Industry</agency_class>
    </lead_sponsor>
  </sponsors>
  <source>Merck Sharp &amp; Dohme Corp.</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      A study to compare pre-operative administration of rofecoxib versus post-operative
      administration of diclofenac or rofecoxib, respectively, in the treatment of post-operative
      pain after total knee joint replacement in patients with osteoarthritis of the knee.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
